feature.name: Brabo
feature.origin: A brave young fellow, who defeated a giant, from Dutch fairy tale.

feature.name: Catafo Saxum
feature.origin: Smart boy, who marked a trail in the woods with corn meal to know the way back, from Cajun (Southern USA) fairy tale.

feature.name: Cendrillon
feature.origin: Protagonist of a fairy tale Cendrillon by French writer Charles Perrault (1697), also known as Cinderella.

feature.name: Ejima Saxum
feature.origin: Seacoast in Japanese fairy tale where fisherman Urashima Taro rescued a turtle and started his journey to the undersea Ryugu Palace.

feature.name: Horai Fossa
feature.origin: Mythical Mount Horai (Penglai in Chinese), paradise of the immortals; in some versions of the Japanese fairy tale about fisherman Urashima is located in the sea on the shell of tortoise that princess Otohime has turned into.

feature.name: Kibidango
feature.origin: Japanese ball-like dumplings made from the flour of the kibi (proso millet) grain that the fairy tale hero Momotaro brought on his distant journey because this sweet keeps its softness for a long time.

feature.name: Kintaro
feature.origin: ‘Golden Boy’ in Japanese fairy tale, who grew up in the wild forests of Mount Ashigara and had a superhuman strength.

feature.name: Kolobok
feature.origin: Small ball-like bun, which ran away from home and rolled on the road, singing his tricky song; protagonist of a Russian fairy tale.

feature.name: Momotaro
feature.origin: ‘Peach Boy’ in Japanese fairy tale, who came to Earth inside a giant peach and once undertook a journey to fight horned ogres in a distant island.

feature.name: Otohime Saxum
feature.origin: Otohime Sama; princess in Japanese fairy tale, sea mistress, who welcomed fisherman Urashima Taro in undersea Ryugu Palace and gave him a parting gift, a jewel box whose lid he was told never to open.

feature.name: Ryujin Dorsum
feature.origin: ‘Dragon god’, sea ruler in Japanese fairy tale, father of princess Otohime, master of the undersea Ryugu Palace where fisherman Urashima Taro was a guest.

feature.name: Tokoyo Fossa
feature.origin: Immortal world of Japanese mythology, eternal, timeless land across the sea or undersea kingdom, where the princess Otohime lives in the fairy tale about the fisherman Urashima.

feature.name: Urashima
feature.origin: Urashima Taro; fisherman in Japanese fairy tale who rescued a turtle and traveled on its back to the dragon Ryujin’s undersea Ryugu Palace, where he was welcomed by princess Otohime.
